🔐 AWS Network ACL (NACL) vs Security Group
A beginner-friendly AWS networking project explaining the differences between **Network ACLs (NACLs)** and **Security Groups**, including architecture, comparison, and a practical hands-on demonstration.

📖 Overview
AWS provides two important security layers to control network traffic:
**Security Groups**         –     Instance-level firewall
**Network ACLs (NACLs)**    –     Subnet-level firewall
This presentation explains how both services work together to secure AWS resources.

